85    // Perform a binary search to get the month. To make it go even faster,
86    // compare using ints instead of longs. The number of milliseconds per
87    // year exceeds the limit of a 32-bit int's capacity, so divide by

89    // milliseconds per day contains 1024 as a factor. After the division,
